**Page Title**: CON - CTF Blue Team Style - SAINTCON

**Description**: This event is a Capture the Flag (CTF) game designed to sharpen blue team cybersecurity skills. It focuses on digital forensics, network forensics, malware analysis, hashing/encryption, threat intelligence, OSINT, scripting, and more.

**Organizer**: NAME OF PERSONS/ORG

**Event Details**:
- **Objective**: Participants will unravel the details of a cyber-attack using provided data to identify vulnerabilities, detect intrusions, and mitigate threats.
- **Game Format**: 
  - Team or solo play (teams of 3-4 members allowed).
  - Access through an online portal to set up teams and submit findings.
  - Compatible with any OS; tools like SANS SIFT Workstation may be utilized.
  - Real-time scoreboard updates.

- **Rules**:
  - Respect the platform; no attacking the scoreboard or other players' challenges.
  - Fair play is mandatory; intentional disruptions are prohibited.
  - Scoring will be dynamic based on challenge difficulty.

- **Who Can Participate**: Open to all skill levels, from beginners to experienced professionals.

**Hours of Operation**:
- **Monday**: Expo Closed
- **Tuesday**: Noon – 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday**: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Thursday**: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Friday**: 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM 

**Icons and Images**: 
- CTF Blue Team logo and promotional graphics are included.

**Links**:
- Official Event Page: [SAINTCON CTF Blue Team Style](https://saintcon.org/con-ctf-blue-team-style/) 
- Social Media and additional resources available on the SAINTCON website.

**Contact**:
- For support and inquiries, details can be found on the event website. 

**Learning and Competition**: 
- Engage and challenge yourself in a dynamic cybersecurity defense environment.